<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.796 Latin American Airways/11:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-14T17:00:00-04:00">May 14, 1929—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>24. Your 59, May 12, 4 p.m. Pending the receipt by it of fuller
                                information as to the status of both parties the Department desires
                                you to adopt a non-committal attitude and assumes that you can do so
                                without jeopardizing the present rights of either.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>